#eNCA speaks to Vhatuka Mbelengwa the founder and spokesperson of the Private Public Transport Association. #eNCA #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - E-hailing drivers across South Africa are planning to shut down major routes and disrupt services in a three-day national strike next week. Drivers affiliated with global app giants like Uber, Bolt, InDriver, and Uber Eats have called on the government to regulate the industry. Vhatuka Mbelengwa, founder and spokesperson of the Private Public Transport Association, says they want the government to cater for their needs as they are being treated unfairly.